        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2178714596" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer725758929472711321">This is a remarkable and horrifying piece of American history that screams to be read! I had never heard of the Osage &quot;Reign of Terror.&quot; This true story is really a dual story; the mass murder of wealthy Osage Indians in Oklahoma for their oil headrights in the 1920s and 30s and the forming of the FBI. <br/><br/>It&apos;s an amazing piece of investigative reporting and very well put together. There are so many characters it can be hard to keep track of who is who, but hang in there. If you think the U.S. is me</span>
  <span id="freeText725758929472711321" style="display:none">This is a remarkable and horrifying piece of American history that screams to be read! I had never heard of the Osage "Reign of Terror." This true story is really a dual story; the mass murder of wealthy Osage Indians in Oklahoma for their oil headrights in the 1920s and 30s and the forming of the FBI. <br /><br />It's an amazing piece of investigative reporting and very well put together. There are so many characters it can be hard to keep track of who is who, but hang in there. If you think the U.S. is messed up now, read this - institutional racism, greed, corruption, conspiracy....and just pure, unadulterated evil.<br /><br />Kudos to David Grann for this scholarly effort and bringing this piece of neglected history to light. I especially treasure the photographs included. It brings the story and the characters to life.</span>
